                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170521-103-off524 t18170521-103-crimeloc527"></join>. On the 29th of April, the bacon was taken out of the shop, between one and two o'clock.</p>
               <p>JOHN THORTON. I am a baker. I met the prisoner in Hatton-wall, with the bacon under his arm, between one and two o'clock of the 29th of April, and stopped him, as I knew him before.</p>
               <p>HANNAH WEST. I live opposite Mr. Vaughan. I saw the prisoner looking in at the window; he went in and brought the bacon out under his arm - I told Mr. Vaughan. He was taken in less than ten minutes.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
